2007-11-23  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Fix various bugs in boostg implementation. 
	* vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg_graph_impl.hh,
	* vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg_graph_impl.hxx: here.
	Update correctly the labels when calling "set_initial" and "set_final".
	has_state() doesn't check anymore whether the pointer contained in a
	hstate_t is in the graph. It just checks whether the integer could refer
	to a state.
	Some cleanup.

2007-11-23  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Add support for deletion while iterating over a boostg container.
	* vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_support.hxx,
	* vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg/vgraph_container.hxx:
	Since we usually iterate over all the states or transitions and 
	some modifications are made in the graph, we want the containers
	to support such operations without invalidating the current iterator.

2007-11-23  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Change the default value of boostg's hstate_t. 
	* vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_handlers.hxx:
	Since the hstate_t are used as integers but are actually a pointer
	and the comparison between two hstate_t is based on the pointed integer,
	we needed a default allocated integer.
	Fix segfaults....

2007-11-23  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Add a new functor to update initial and final state's label.
	* vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_functors.hxx: here.

2007-11-23  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Temporarily replace set<htransition_t> by list<htransition_t>. 
	* vaucanson/algorithms/aut_to_exp.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/evaluation.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/internal/outsplitting.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/internal/skeleton.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/is_deterministic.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/letter_to_letter_composition.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/normalized.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/normalized_composition.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/product.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/standard.hxx,
	* vaucanson/algorithms/sum.hxx:
	Since I need a working version for today, I need to fix quickly
	some issues. currently I have an issue when I want to store boostg's
	htransition_t which store iterators. Sometimes two iterators are
	identical, thus transitions are missing in the set... I don't know
	why yet. My guess is that Boost uses the same iterator when there are
	duplicates.
	Anyway, I will change the delta* methods soon and this bug should be
	fixed at the same time.

2007-11-22  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Add new operators for boostg's hstate_t 
	* vaucanson/automata/concept/handlers.hxx,
	* vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_handlers.hh,
	* vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_handlers_op.hxx:
	We want the hstate_t to behave like real integers even though they are
	actually pointers in the boostg implementation. Thus we needed proper
	operators for comparison.
	We also wanted to always display them as integer when passed to
	std::cout.

2007-11-21  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Fix various bugs and update the method's prototype in boostg implementation. 
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg_graph_impl.hh,
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/boostg_graph_impl.hxx: here.
	The state deletion and the delta* were incorrect.
	Add more preconditions.
	Use iterator instead of pointers in htransition_t. It is faster and safer.
	It may be slower in delta* since htransition_t are copied in a container.
	However a solution is going to be applied soon :D

