	copies of such objects. Thus, I changed the prototypes of every op_*
	functions.

2007-11-21  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Move implementation's specific code into its own directory. 
	* automata/implementation/boostg/boost_functors.hxx: Remove,
	* automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_functors.hxx: New,
	* automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_handlers.hh: New,
	* automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_handlers.hxx: New,
	* automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_handlers_op.hxx: New,
	* automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_support.hh: New,
	* automata/implementation/boostg/boostg_support.hxx: New,
	* automata/implementation/boostg/edge_value.hxx,
	* automata/implementation/boostg/initial_value.hxx,
	* automata/implementation/boostg/vgraph_container.hxx,
	* misc/support.hh,
	* misc/support.hxx:
	The boostg implementation need specializations of objects provided by
	Vaucanson. In order to clearly identify which specialization is related
	to which implementation, I decided to move the related code in a
	directory named like the implementation.
	This code need a serious cleanup. I'll do it next weeks. Be patient :p

2007-11-15  Guillaume Lazzara  <z@lrde.epita.fr>

	Remove hstate_t's dependency on integer.
	* include/Makefile.am: include new files in the tarball.

	* include/vaucanson/automata/concept/handlers.hh,
	* include/vaucanson/automata/concept/handlers.hxx:
	This type declaration is a generic one which can be
	specialized as needed. A handler must be convertible to an unsigned
	and the constructor based on the contained type _must_ be explicitly
	called.

	* include/vaucanson/automata/concept/automata_base.hh,
	* include/vaucanson/automata/concept/automata_base.hxx,
	* include/vaucanson/automata/concept/automata_ops.hh,
	* include/vaucanson/automata/concept/automata_ops.hxx,
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/automaton_view.hxx:
      	Introduce a new operator 'op_get_state'. The graph structure
	is now used as a builder for hstate_t objects.
	Since we want to refer to states both with integer and hstate_t we
	also provide two versions of each operator handling states.

	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/legacy_graph_impl.hh: .
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/legacy_graph_impl.hxx: .
	Add new preconditions and use unsigned instead of signed integer as IDs
	for the states.

	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/legacy/legacy_handlers.hh: New.
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/legacy/legacy_handlers.hxx: New.
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/legacy/legacy_sparse_interval.hh: New.
	* include/vaucanson/automata/implementation/legacy/legacy_sparse_interval.hxx: New.
	Split previous automata/concept/handlers.* and misc/sparce_interval.*
	files and move the code related to the legacy implementation in these
	new files.
	SparseInterval::max() has been removed and replaced by
	SparseInterval::back() for a better compatibility with STL containers.


	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/eps_removal.hxx: .
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/eval.hxx: .
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/minimization_hopcroft.hxx: .
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/minimization_moore.hxx: .
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/realtime.hxx: .
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/search.hxx: .
	* include/vaucanson/algorithms/standard_of.hxx: .
	Various fixes to make these algorithms work with 'generic' hstate_t
	variables. Basically, we just needed to replace calls to
	SparseInterval::max(). 

	* include/vaucanson/misc/random.hh: .
	* include/vaucanson/misc/random.hxx: .
	* include/vaucanson/tools/automaton_tools.hh: .
	* include/vaucanson/tools/gen_random.hxx: .
	Make the random function dependent on the data type of the container.

	* taf-kit/src/edition_commands.hxx: make use of the get_state function.

